ENGL 4687 - Practicum in Teaching English as a
Second/Foreign Language
Internship-like experience for prospective teachers of learners of
English. Student will be under the supervision of TESL faculty and an
administrator at the location where English is taught to children or adults.
Course can be offered as a Study Abroad course.
Prerequisite: ENGL 4377 and ENGL 4378, or consent of instructor.
Course includes a practicum of at least 50 hours.
